desc:
This week the SAP crew gets a message from a fan in Australia, and Oscar poses the question, “What is the most definitive Latinx movie?”. Carlos, Tony, Raiza and Oscar all weigh in on their favorite films and discuss white-washing, and the importance Latinx people rising up together in the film industry. Then, Lauren Ashley Smith (The Rundown, Black Lady Sketch Show ) stops by to talk about her hilarious new HBO show, how she met her wife, and all things equestrian. And if there was nothing else Ashley couldn’t do, she pony’s up and joins the SAP crew for some improv fun. 
Follow everyone here!
